<br>
I want to get rid of the salt I boil the water and use a bowl or wax paper to catch the vapors. <br>
IF you use a bowl you have to have a bigger bowl underneith it all to catch the water  as it steams off the bowl<br>
<br>
If you use the wax paper you can angle it to all drip off 4 corners.<br>
<br>
after you do this long enough you have clean water.<br>
Learned this long ago when I went camping.<br>
Did it myself and it works.<br>
<br>
if you do it enough times you get some cool looking salt cystals in the pan.<br>
<br>
To do this to provide for the population you would just have to up the scale.<br>
<br>
only cost would be builing the place, and cost of cleaning out the Giant bowl of the salt cystals.<br>
<br>
Now again this will work for salt water, no clue if it would work for polluted salt water. Never tried.<br>
